## Limitations

The analysis is limited by the availability of recent and comprehensive studies specifically addressing the complexity of expectancy theory in organizational settings. Additionally, the subjective nature of the theory means that its applicability can vary significantly across different organizational contexts and individual perceptions. Further empirical research could provide more insights into the practical challenges and solutions for implementing expectancy theory effectively.